There is another definite φ ownership inconsistency in the standard NUTS target: it scales the Gaussian likelihood by `1/φ` and scales the whitening by `√φ`, but the precomputed penalty contribution is left unscaled. The link-wiggle target explicitly applies the matching penalty scale, so I’m checking line references and whether the same issue exists in other HMC paths.
